It has navigated over the ocean to land in the hands of the [...]]]></summary>
    <content type="html" xml:base="http://blog.nexwerk.com/2009/06/24/the-wandering-book/"><![CDATA[<p>A couple of weeks ago I released <a href="http://www.nexwerk.com/the_wandering_book/">The Wandering Book</a> to the world after announcing it on the Craftsmen Meetup in Chicago which I joined via iChat videoconferencing.</p>
<p>What I missed to announce is that the book has actually started it&#8217;s journey already! </p>
<p>It has navigated over the ocean to land in the hands of the first craftsman to write down his thoughts about the craft. </p>
<p>I was actually very glad to see that the first person who is compiling his thoughts into the wandering book will be <a href="http://www.coreyhaines.com">Corey Haines</a>, the first every journeyman in the Software Craftsmanship Community who spends his time really journeying from company to company learning from them their techniques and sharing his knowledge. I am sure his ideas in the book will be worth gold! <img src='http://blog.nexwerk.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif' alt=':)' class='wp-smiley' /> </p>
<p>You can view the pages the craftsmen have written once they upload them to the companion site and pass the book over to the next craftsman (<a href="http://www.nexwerk.com/the_wandering_book/view">view the book</a>).</p>
]]></content>
